The Regulatory Flexibility Act (5 U.S.C. 601 
et seq.
) requires preparation of a final regulatory flexibility analysis (âFRFAâ) for any final rule where the agency was first required by law to publish a proposed rule for public comment, unless the agency certifies that the rule will not have a significant economic impact on a substantial number of small entities. As required by E.O. 13272, âProper Consideration of Small Entities in Agency Rulemaking,â 67 FR 53461 (Aug. 16, 2002), DOE published procedures and policies on February 19, 2003, to ensure that the potential impacts of its rules on small entities are properly considered during the rulemaking process. 68 FR 7990. DOE has made its procedures and policies available on the Office of the General Counsel's website (
www.energy.gov/gc/office-general-counsel
